</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usliver123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sliver123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 3:28:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1286.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh wow</span><hr size=1> The method I like is when a master looter loots all items and cash (make sure it is someone you can trust) and at the end of the group or when members leave/join, is to /split the cash, and /random 100. Highest roll picks an item, second picks the next, thrid next and so on. <br>
Pre-empting that is if someone can use an item and it would be an upgrade, they get it. If 2 or more are in the same boat, roll and pick.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uveloxiavoluptuous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veloxia Voluptuous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 297<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/6/02 3:37:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1286.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oh wow</span><hr size=1> WOW Sliver.... in my 3 years of EQ, i have never seen roll and pick as an addition to NBG(or without NBG). I think i will use that in my future groups! seems alot more fair than winning a little item, then a big item drops and you cant roll... and alot simpler than rolling on the 2nd item and if you win, giving up the 1st item to be rolled on again. in places like Seb Crypt... that gets frustrating. <p><BR><B>Veloxia Voluptuous </B><BR>
